Thanks for the fix @wxiaoguang, I just tested the nightly build but there is still some issues. 

In my case a user has a repository with folders as submodules, but the source does not exist anymore (404).

Gitea v1.24.2 shows the full repository with all files/folders and submodule commit id.

Gitea v1.24.3 throws a 500 and does not show anything at all

Gitea v1.24-nightly throws a 500 but shows every folder/file until the submodule folder, the submodule commit id link is not shown and the rest of the output is broken.

